sentences: Elaine Hugh-Jones (14 June 1927 – 29 March 2021) was a Welsh pianist, music educator and composer.
After completing her studies, she took a position as an accompanist with the BBC, where she worked for 37 years.
Winter (in Six de la Mare Songs) (Text: Walter de la Mare)Hugh-Jones' songs were broadcast on BBC Radio 3 and have been recorded and released on CD, including:
Poésie et musique au féminin (The Feminine in Poetry and Music) Audio CD (9 April 2002)
